Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the deployment and performance aspects of the system based on the repository summary:

```plantuml
@startuml michaelsrichter_azure.owasp

actor User
participant "Azure AD" as AAD
participant "Load Balancer" as LB
participant "Web Application Firewall" as WAF
participant "ASP.NET MVC App" as MVC
participant "Node.js App" as Node
database "Azure SQL Database" as DB

User -> LB: HTTP Request
LB -> WAF: Forward Request
WAF -> WAF: Apply ModSecurity Rules
alt Request Blocked
    WAF --> User: Block Request
else Request Allowed
    WAF -> MVC: Forward to ASP.NET MVC App
    activate MVC
    MVC -> AAD: Authenticate User
    AAD --> MVC: Return Token
    MVC -> MVC: Validate Token
    MVC -> DB: Query Data
    DB --> MVC: Return Data
    MVC --> WAF: HTTP Response
    deactivate MVC
end
WAF -> WAF: Apply ModSecurity Rules
WAF --> LB: Forward Response
LB --> User: HTTP Response

@enduml
```